caption.p: Incidence rate (cases per 100,000 population) and averaged number of dengue cases reported in District of Gampaha, Sri Lanka. Green color indicates the MOH areas with low dengue incidences rates, yellow indicates those with medium incidences rates, and red those with high incidences rates, from 2005 to 2014. The red colored dots indicate the average number of dengue cases reported in the each MOH area in this period
